vertex shader:

the vertex shader is responsible for transforming the vertices of the 3d model into the 2d screen coordinates. The vertex shader also calculates the direction vector of the ray that is cast from the camera to the 3d model.

here is a basic outline of the vertex shader code:

```
#version 330

in vec4 aVertexPosition;

uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;

out vec3 vNormal;
out vec3 vLightDirection;
out vec3 vViewDirection;
out vec3 vRayDirection;

