Next, let's define our account types and their corresponding strategies:

```
class CheckingAccountStrategy implements IAccountStrategy {
    public void deposit(double amount) {
        System.out.println("Deposit of $" + amount + " made to checking account.");
    }

    public void withdraw(double amount) {
        System.out.println("Withdrawal of $" + amount + " made from checking account.");
    }
}

class SavingsAccountStrategy implements IAccountStrategy {
    public void deposit(double amount) {
        System.out.println("Deposit of $" + amount + " made to savings account.");
    }

    public void withdraw(double amount) {
        System.out.println("Withdrawal of $" + amount + " made from savings account.");
    }
}

class CheckingAccountTypeStrategy implements IAccountTypeStrategy {
    public IAccountStrategy getAccountStrategy() {
        return new CheckingAccountStrategy();
    }
}

class SavingsAccountTypeStrategy implements IAccountTypeStrategy {
    public IAccountStrategy getAccountStrategy() {
        return new SavingsAccountStrategy();
    }
}
```

Now let's create our banking app system:

```
class BankingAppSystem {
    private IAccountTypeStrategy accountTypeStrategy;

    public BankingAppSystem(IAccountTypeStrategy accountTypeStrategy) {
        this.accountTypeStrategy = accountTypeStrategy;
    }

    public void deposit(double amount) {
        IAccountStrategy accountStrategy = accountTypeStrategy.getAccountStrategy();
        accountStrategy.deposit(amount);
    }

    public void withdraw(double amount) {
        IAccountStrategy accountStrategy = accountTypeStrategy.getAccountStrategy();
        accountStrategy.withdraw(amount);
    }
}

public class Main {
