Here's a simple C# program that extracts hashtags from a given text:

```csharp
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        Console.Write("Enter some text: ");
        string text = Console.ReadLine();

        string[] hashtags = text.Split(new[] { '#' }, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries);

        Console.WriteLine("Hashtags:");
        foreach (string hashtag in hashtags)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("#" + hashtag);
        }
    }
}
```

This program prompts the user to enter some text, then splits the text into an array of strings using the "#" character as a delimiter. Finally, the program prints out each hashtag in the array, prefixed with the "#" character.

To add a new user based on the web API, you can use JavaScript to make an API call when the button is clicked. Here's an example:

